{{Infobox language |name=Zotung |nativename=''Zotung'' |region=[[Rezua]], [[Chin State]] |states=[[Burma]] |ethnicity=[[Zotung people|Zo]] (''Zotung Minphuin'') |speakers=52,000 |date=1990 |ref = e18 |family= Tinpaw Boi |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Kuki-Chin languages|Kuki-Chin]] |fam4=[[Maraic languages|Maraic]] |iso3=czt |glotto=zotu1235 |glottorefname=Zotung Chin }} '''Zotung''' (Zo Minphuin, Chin) is a [[Kuki-Chin languages|Kuki-Chin language]] spoken in [[Rezua]] subtownship, [[Chin State]], [[Burma]].
